user.biography:
If you could use a little bit of joy & laughter, you've come to the right place! Tuna’s travels follow @thetravelingtuna
REQUEST CAMEO VIDEO HERE 👇

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and dog.

node.text: Did you know that I’m American (although I’m an Anglophile) and Tuna’s dad is British? So do you think that Tuna has an American or British accent? Head to his stories to hear (and see) for yourself and then comment below. 🇺🇸🇬🇧

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} in Trafalgar Square London with @martinjamesbushell.

node.text: It was #sharkweek a couple weeks ago, and next week we head to the UK where this sculpture hopefully still remains. Firstly, how did I miss this #tunainterpretations masterpiece because I would have DEFINITELY posted about it during #sharkweek, and secondly, I really hope this is in public because I will March over to Trafalgar Square to see it! Please let me know, @martinjamesbushell, and thank you so much for this incredible creation!

node.text: We are leaving in one week from today to visit our family across the pond. Unfortunately Tuna isn’t able to come with us this time, which breaks my heart, but he’ll be in the excellent care of his auntie Wendy and in the company of his beloved brother, Fisch. For this week only I put @cameo back up, so if you want a personalised video from him for someone you love, now is the time :) If you miss this window, they’ll be available again at the end of August. Link in his bio!

node.text: #ad Tuna loved the Original Series of Turner & Hooch on @disneyplus so much that he wanted to review it by reenacting it. As you can see, the new reboot is wildly entertaining, action-packed, hilarious, and family-friendly! Not to mention it’s adorable, thanks to slobbery Hooch. To stream the Original #TurnerAndHoochSeries on #DisneyPlus starring @shuapeck as Scott Turner, visit the link in Tuna’s bio or go to Tuna’s Stories and swipe up!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} on July 22, 2021. May be an image of dog.

node.text: This sweet little angel face baby head got his remaining stitches removed today, so he wanted to model his face to show off. I seriously cannot reiterate how relieved and thankful I am that his markings were all benign! A MASSIVE THANK YOU, again, to Dr. Schick and her amazing team at Atlanta Veterinary Specialists. They are phenomenal and took SUCH great care of my baby. I couldn’t be happier with them and their services! 👏🙌

Did you know that we were given the opportunity to license and manufacture the Colin dolls for a limited time, exclusive to Tunameltsmyheart. For those who signed up for the Colin pre-sale details about a month ago, we will be sending out an email and posting more about that here in the coming weeks! If you haven’t signed up to be the first to get on the pre-sale list, go to the link in the bio to sign up for that under COLIN PRE-SALE SIGN UP! Stay Tuna’d.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Tuna {breed:chiweenie} on July 20, 2021 tagging @camilla_kitten. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: Since today commemorates the day man first walked on the moon in 1969 and it’s also the day that Jeff Bezos launched into space for like 10 minutes, I thought that this was an appropriate compilation to post for #nationalmoonday and #tunartuesdays. All of these epic #tunainterpretations are by @camilla_kitten @psyca @marsorbust83. Which do #astroTUNAut do you like best? 1, 2, or 3? 👨‍🚀

Tomorrow is #nationaltattooday but I have something else planned to post so we’re celebrating this today! I’m not sure how many people in the world have Tuna tattooed on their bodies but if you do, you are THE COOLEST in my books, just like @saralukestar is. 
Artist: @linnaasne of @treehouse_tattoo in Norway. 
If you have a Tuna tat or are an artist who has one that you’ve done before, please comment below that you have one (just say I DO!) Please post a photo of it and tag #tunainterpretations or post in your stories and tag @tunameltsmyheart so I can repost it. I’d love to see it! Next question: Would you get someone else’s dog tattooed on your body?

node.text: Wanna “see” something amazing? #eyepun 👁🤪. Swipe over ⬅️. That’s what Tuna’s eye looked like a couple of months ago and the first photo is what it looks like today! 😱 So so thankful to God that the marking was benign and not malignant. So thankful for you for partnering with me in praying and for your support & encouragement. And so grateful to Dr. Schick at Atlanta Veterinary Specialists for removing his markings (he had two others) with such precision! He looks like a new boy!

node.text: I just found out that all of his markings are BENIGN AND his cone can come off!!! PTL 🙏🙌🥳 This has been such a long two weeks waiting for the results, but I am so relieved with this report and so thankful! Thank you for all of your prayers and encouragement! I cannot stress enough how pleased and impressed I am with how precise and professional Dr. Schick and her RVT, Jennifer, were/are! They did such an amazing job on all three sites (his eye and two on top of his head) that you would hardly know anything was there, especially by his eye. Seriously, y’all, if you live in the Atlanta-area or in a city near by and need an awesome pet Dermatology Specialist, look them up: Atlanta Veterinary Specialists (atlvet.com). They are not general vets but they specialise in anything dermatology related and they are THE BEST!
